ce.splitn` still uses the `usize` parameter as the maximum number of items to return. Both methods are stable.\n\nThis inconsistency could possibly be way more confusing than having them both one way or the other.\n\nExcerpt from `str.splitn` documentation (http://doc.rust-lang.org/std/primitive.str.html#method.splitn)\n\n```\nAn iterator over substrings of self, separated by characters matched by a pattern, returning most count items.\n```\n\nFrom `slice.splitn` documentation (http://doc.rust-lang.org/std/primitive.slice.html#method.splitn):\n\n```\nReturns an iterator over subslices separated by elements that match pred, limited to returning at most n items. The matched element is not contained in the subslices.\n```\n", "closed_by": {"login": "daboross", "id": 1152146, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjExNTIxNDY=", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/1152146?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/daboross", "html_url": "https://github.com/daboross", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/daboross/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/daboross/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/daboross/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/daboross/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/daboross/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/daboross/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/daboross/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/daboross/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/daboross/received_events", "type": "User", "site_admin": false}, "reactions": {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/24082/reactions", "total_count": 0, "+1": 0, "-1": 0, "laugh": 0, "hooray": 0, "confused": 0, "heart": 0, "rocket": 0, "eyes": 0}, "timeline_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/24082/timeline", "performed_via_github_a